Privacy Policy

Effective Date: December 31, 2024

AI Recipe Finder ("we," "our," or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy describes how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our app ("App"). Please read this policy carefully to understand our practices regarding your personal data.

Information We Collect

1. Information You Provide to Us:

Personal Information: When you register or interact with our App, we may collect personal data such as your name, email address, phone number, or other details you voluntarily provide.

Payment Information: If our App involves purchases, we may collect payment details such as credit card information (processed by a third-party payment gateway).

2. Information We Collect Automatically:

Device Information: We collect information about the device you use to access the App, including IP address, device type, operating system, and browser type.

Usage Data: We collect data about your interactions with the App, such as pages viewed, features used, and session duration.

Cookies and Tracking Technologies: We may use cookies, beacons, and similar technologies to track activity on our App.

3. Information from Third Parties:

We may collect information about you from third-party sources, such as social media platforms, if you connect your account to the App.

How We Use Your Information

We use the information we collect for the following purposes:

To provide, maintain, and improve our App.

To process transactions and send related information.

To communicate with you, including sending notifications and responding to inquiries.

To personalize your experience and deliver tailored content.

To ensure the security and integrity of the App.

To comply with legal obligations and enforce our terms and conditions.

Sharing Your Information

We do not sell your personal data. However, we may share your information in the following circumstances:

With Service Providers: We may share your data with third-party service providers who perform functions on our behalf (e.g., hosting, payment processing).

In Legal Matters: We may disclose your information to comply with legal obligations or protect our rights and interests.

With Your Consent: We may share your information with third parties when you have provided explicit consent.

Data Retention

We retain your personal data only for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this policy, comply with legal obligations, or resolve disputes.

Security of Your Information

We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your personal data. However, no method of transmission or storage is completely secure. Use of the App is at your own risk.

Your Rights

Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have rights regarding your personal data, including:

The right to access, update, or delete your information.

The right to withdraw consent where processing is based on your consent.

The right to object to certain processing activities.

To exercise your rights, contact us at [Insert Contact Information].

Third-Party Links

Our App may contain links to third-party websites or services. We are not responsible for the privacy practices of such third parties. We encourage you to review their privacy policies.

Updates to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of significant changes by posting the updated policy within the App or through other communication channels.

Contact Us

